definition.value: A dipeptide formed from L-arginine and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-asparagine and L-glutamic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-asparagine and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-glutamine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-glutamic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-lysine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-phenylalanine residues. It is obtained after the hydrolysis of aspartame in intestinal lumen.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-tryptophan residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-aspartyl and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from beta-alanine and L-alanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from beta-alanine and glycine residues.
A dipeptide formed from beta-alanine and L-phenylalanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from D-alanine and glycine residues.
A tripeptide composed of one D-alanine and two glycine residues joined in sequence.
A dipeptide formed from D-alanine and L-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from two D-leucine residues.
A dipeptide formed from D-leucine and glycine residues.
A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl group contains 16 carbons and no additional double bonds.
A dipeptide formed from D-leucine and L-tyrosine residues.
A dipeptide formed from D-gamma-glutamyl and glycine residues.

An N(4)-glycosylated L-asparagine residue in which the glycosyl element is a branched  dodecasaccharide comprising a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl (1->6)]-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl chain, to the mannosyl residue of which are linked (1->3) and (1->6) two alpha-sialyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl units.
A glutamyl-L-amino acid obtained by formal condensation of the gamma-carboxy group of glutamic acid with the amino group of glycine.
A dipeptide formed from two L-glutamine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-glutamine and L-glutamic acid residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-glutamine and glycine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-alpha-glutamyl and L-alanine residues.
A  lysophosphatidylcholine P-16:0 in which the alk-1-enyl group is hexadec-1-en-1-yl.
A  1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group is (9Z)-hexadecenoyl (palmitoleoyl).
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-3-oxodocosatetraenoyl-CoA.

A lysophosphatidylcholine in which the remaining acyl group contains 17 carbons and 1 double bond. If R1 is acyl and R2 is a hydrogen then the molecule is a 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine. If R1 is a hydrogen and R2 is acyl then the molecule is a 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
A  1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the  1-acyl group is (10Z)-heptadecenoyl.
A dipeptide formed from glycine and L-alanine residues.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl-CoA
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-3-oxotetracosatetraenoyl-CoA.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:0 in which the acyl substituent is located at position 1 and is specified as stearoyl.
A dialkylglycerophosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl groups are hexadecyl and the glycerol core has sn stereochemistry with the phosphoethanolamine unit at position 3.
A dipeptide formed from glycine and L-arginine residues.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoyl-CoA.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-3-oxodocosapentaenoyl-CoA.

An N-glycosylated dialkylglycerophosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl groups are hexadecyl, the glycerol core has sn stereochemistry and the phosphoethanolamine unit is at position 3 and substituted on nitrogen with the branched undecasaccharide alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
A phosphatidylcholine 40:5 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are octadecanoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoyl respectively.
A dialkylglycerophosphoethanolamine in which the amine group is substituted by a glycosyl group.

An N-glycosylated dialkylglycerophosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl groups are hexadecyl, the glycerol core has sn stereochemistry and the phosphoethanolamine unit is at position 3 and substituted on nitrogen with the branched nonasaccharide beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
A phosphatidylcholine 40:6 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are (11Z)-octadecenoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoyl respectively.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoyl-CoA.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-oxotetracosapentaenoyl-CoA.

An N-glycosylated dialkylglycerophosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl groups are hexadecyl, the glycerol core has sn stereochemistry and the phosphoethanolamine unit is at position 3 and substituted on nitrogen with the branched heptasaccharide beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
